  98:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\drivers/peripheral/tcpwm/cy_tcpwm.h **** * A quadrature decoder is used to decode the output of a quadrature encoder. 
  99:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\drivers/peripheral/tcpwm/cy_tcpwm.h **** * A quadrature encoder senses the position, velocity, and direction of 
 100:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\drivers/peripheral/tcpwm/cy_tcpwm.h **** * an object (for example a rotating axle, or a spinning mouse ball). 
 101:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\drivers/peripheral/tcpwm/cy_tcpwm.h **** * A quadrature decoder can also be used for precision measurement of speed, 
